'''Baramotichi Vihir''' is a stepwell in [[Limb, Satara]] village in [[Satara district]] in [[Maharashtra]] state in [[India]]. It was constructed between 1641 and 1646 by Virubai Bhosale. It is 110 ft deep and 50 ft in diameter. Limb village is situated around 16 km from [[Satara (city)|Satara]] and approximately 99 km from [[Pune]]. The well is octagonal in shape and looks like dug-out [[Shivling]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news-frec/MH-MUM-OMC-fort-inside-well-in-baramoti-well-satara-5247889-PHO.html|title=fort inside well in baramoti well satara - www.bhaskar.com|work=dainikbhaskar|accessdate=13 February 2016}}</ref>

