{{coord|50.5277|-4.5710|display=title}} [[File:Colliford Lake 05.jpg|thumb|right|Colliford Lake]] [[File:Colliford Lake NW end on Bodmin Moor - geograph.org.uk - 130232.jpg|Northwest end of Colliford Lake|thumb]] '''Colliford Lake''' is a [[reservoir]] on [[Bodmin Moor]], [[Cornwall]], England, United Kingdom. Covering more than {{convert|900|acre|km2}},<ref>[http://www.cornwall-calling.co.uk/fishing.htm Cornwall Calling website. Retrieved April 2010]</ref> it is the second-largest lake in Cornwall.<ref>[https://www.visitcornwall.com/things-to-do/bodmin-moor-tamar-valley/bodmin/colliford-lake Colliford Lake], Visit Cornwall, accessed 28 December 2015</ref> It is situated south of the [[A30 road|A30]] trunk road near the village of [[Bolventor]], the approximate centre of the lake being at {{oscoor|SX179730|OS grid reference SX179730}}.<ref>Ordnance Survey: Landranger map sheet 201 ''Plymouth & Launceston'' {{ISBN|978-0-319-23146-3}}</ref> [[Dozmary Pool]] outfalls into the lake and the lake's own outfall forms one of the tributaries of the [[River Fowey]].
The northernmost point of the lake is approximately three-quarters of a mile (1&nbsp;km) south of Bolventor at {{oscoor|SX184756|OS grid reference SX184756}} and the [[dam|headbank]] at the southernmost point is approximately three miles (5&nbsp;km) south of Bolventor at {{oscoor|SX177709|OS grid reference SX177709}}.<ref>Ordnance Survey: Explorer map sheet 109 ''Bodmin Moor'' {{ISBN|978-0-319-24047-2}}</ref>
Leisure facilities on the site include [[angling]] and a {{convert|50|acre|m2|adj=on}} adventure and nature park, Colliford Lake Park,<ref>[http://www.collifordlakepark.co.uk Colliford Lake Park]</ref> which features trails and footpaths, play areas, wetlands, picnic areas and a cafe.<ref>[http://search.visitbritain.com/en-EN/Details.aspx?contentID=132694&IsSearchFormAccommodation=false Visit Britain website; Colliford Lake; retrieved April 2010]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Colliford Lake is managed by the [[South West Lakes Trust]], an environmental and recreational charity which manages fifty inland water sites in Cornwall, Devon, and Somerset.<ref>[http://www.swlakestrust.org.uk/home South West Lakes Trust website. Retrieved April 2010]</ref>
